HEADWORD: Incameration
<hw>In*cam`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + L. <ets>camera</ets> chamber, LL., also,
jurisdiction: cf. F. <ets>incam⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>, It.
<ets>incamerazione</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The act or
process of uniting lands, rights, or revenues, to the ecclesiastical
chamber, <it>i. e.</it>, to the pope's domain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

